# Tailwind CSS Standards

## Responsive Design
- Always mobile-first: base styles for mobile, sm: for 640px+, md: for 768px+, lg: for 1024px+, xl: for 1280px+
- Use fluid typography with clamp() when possible
- Test at 320px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px breakpoints

## Spacing & Layout
- Use Tailwind's spacing scale consistently (don't mix arbitrary values unless necessary)
- Prefer gap-* over margin for flex/grid children
- Use container with mx-auto and px-4 for page-level containers

## Colors & Theming
- Define brand colors in tailwind.config as CSS variables
- Use semantic color names (primary, secondary, accent, muted)
- Always check contrast ratios for accessibility

## Typography
- Use font-sans for body, font-display (or a custom display font) for headings
- Ensure readable line-height (leading-relaxed for body text)
- Max line width: max-w-prose for long-form content

## Patterns to Avoid
- Never use @apply in component files (defeats utility-first purpose)
- Never use !important — restructure instead
- Avoid deeply nested arbitrary values — extend config instead
